dct_description_sm: This polygon data layer represents VHF Public Coast Station Areas (VPCs) for Wisconsin in 2002. The dataset was originally published by the Federal Communications Commission in 2002.[The VHF Public Coast Station Areas (VPCs) which were created by Commission staff are an aggregation of BEAs into 42 areas, including the Gulf of Mexico (4). VPCs 1-9 are called Maritime VPCs and VPCs 10-42 are called Inland Areas. The Maritime VPCs are an aggregation of one or more BEAs and the Inland Areas are defined as exactly one BEA.]
